- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language modeling and incorporates morphological supervision into character language models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses multitasking to improve performance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with improving language modeling performance. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks for language modeling. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with sound or audio data.
